WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:15.000
Today I'm going to walk through how Anthropic's Claude 3.5 Sonnet handles
extended thinking on complex reasoning tasks.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:35.000
We'll cover three benchmarks: GSM8K, MMLU, and HumanEval. Claude 3.5 Sonnet
scores 96.4% on GSM8K, 88.7% on MMLU, and 92% on HumanEval when extended
thinking is enabled.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:55.000
The key architectural insight is that Claude is given a scratchpad where it
can spend up to 64,000 tokens reasoning before emitting the final answer.
This is similar to OpenAI's o1 approach but with a different training
objective focused on faithful chain-of-thought.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:15.000
Target audience: ML engineers evaluating reasoning models for production
workloads where correctness matters more than latency.
